CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 22, 1969, pg. 8, reads: "Those Rampaging Lincoln-Larimer Panthers - Coached by Joe Golden, the Lincoln-Larimer starters (above) constitute one of the nation's top 130-pound limit elevens.  In from array (Left to right) are James Payton, Charles Jackson, Keth Randal, Tony Reed, Bruce Lesesne, Alfred Glaye, Ronald Johnson.  In the backfield are Ricardo Cobb, Brian Mills, Tony James, Bran Peeks and Arthur Blackburn.  The latter and James serve as captains."
TitMainTitle: Lincoln-Larimer Panthers boys football team members including James Payton, Charles Jackson, Keith Randal, Tony Reed, Bruce Lesesne, Alfred Glaye, Ronald Johnson, Ricardo Cobb, Brian Mills, Tony James, Bran Peeks, and Arthur Blackburn posed on field at night
